Ask HN: Does anyone have a second remote dev job on top of their main one?
text:
Given the hyper efficient documentation search that is chatgpt, I feel like I can easily knock out code for a second remote job in the spare time I have off my main one.

Is there any way for companies to find out that I am double dipping, and can they do anything about it?

Tell: Google search is getting worse
text:
It seems that Google is suffering from gpt influence, and started putting gpt everywhere.

I was searching certain words and the interface drastically changes based on what they think of the word. Then again, the auto completion is apparent hack of some gpt models in a rush.

It really used to be cool and stable, at least for me. Deep learning is not a magic hammer.
